# STRATEGICLAND — Sound Behavior System

> Sound is **the air the room remembers**.
> The audience must feel the space, not hear the website.
> If a soundtrack makes a moment "feel cinematic", that moment was **not** cinematic to begin with.

---

## 1. Audio Philosophy

- Sound exists to **deepen presence**, not to **perform emotion**.
- The default state of the project is **silence**. Audio is **opt-in**. Always.
- Sound is **environmental**, not narrative. We do not score the experience — we **populate the room**.
- The audience must feel that they are listening to the **space**, not to the **content**.
- If sound were removed, the experience must still hold. Sound is **not load-bearing**.

This rule pre-architects audio for the project. Implementation may follow later, but the **shape** is locked now to prevent the future temptation of adding cinematic music ("just for the hero").

---

## 2. Sound Categories (LOCKED)

The project allows **only** these categories. Any audio that doesn't fit one of these is **forbidden**.

| Category                  | Role                                              | Examples                                          |
|---------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
| **Room tone**             | Continuous low-amplitude environmental presence   | Distant traffic; air movement; analog hum         |
| **Atmospheric drift**     | Slow-evolving ambient texture                     | Wind across stone; water far away; forest air     |
| **Spatial resonance**     | Single, infrequent, low-mid frequency event       | Door closing in distance; bell decay; rain pulse  |
| **Transition resonance**  | Sub-audible low-frequency wash during chapter cut | 40–80 Hz sub rumble, 1.8s decay                   |
| **Tactile micro-tone**    | Sub-audible response to deliberate interactions   | 1.2s decay tone on chapter index open             |
| **Silence states**        | Engineered absences (room cuts to dead air)       | TIER 01 scenes; mid-chapter holds                 |

### Categories explicitly forbidden
- ❌ **Music** — orchestral, electronic, ambient with melody, drone synths.
- ❌ **Voice / narration** (unless an editorial chapter explicitly carries an interview piece, in which case it is content, not soundtrack).
- ❌ **Foley / SFX** — clicks, swooshes, "whooshes", tap clicks.
- ❌ **Notification sounds** — chimes, dings, alerts.
- ❌ **Cinematic stings** — riser/impact pairs.
- ❌ **Lo-fi / vinyl crackle** — costume sound, not real environment.

---

## 3. Sound Sources & Production Standards

### 3.1 Source material
- All audio is **field-recorded** (analog or digital field recorder), never synthesized melodically.
- Allowed synth use: **sub-bass** layer (40–80 Hz) for transition resonance, **always** mixed under a field recording.
- Source recordings come from:
  - Real spaces relevant to the project's narrative (architectural interiors, landscapes, urban edges).
  - Public domain field libraries (with provenance attribution in `content/audio/credits.mdx`).

### 3.2 Mixing / mastering
| Property              | Constraint                                              |
|-----------------------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| Peak level            | ≤ -18 dB LUFS integrated                                |
| True peak             | ≤ -3 dBTP                                               |
| Dynamic range         | ≥ 9 LU (preserve breath; no broadcast compression)      |
| Sample rate           | 48 kHz                                                  |
| Bit depth (delivery)  | 16-bit AAC (96 kbps) for ambience, 192 kbps for transition resonance |
| File format           | `.m4a` (AAC) primary, `.opus` fallback for modern browsers |
| Loudness consistency  | All tracks normalized to **-23 LUFS** integrated         |
| Stereo image          | Mid-heavy (no extreme L/R panning); width factor ≤ 0.6  |
| Sub content           | High-pass at 30 Hz (avoid sub-audible noise on phone speakers) |
| Loop discipline       | Seamless cross-fade loops (≥ 4s overlap), no audible seam |

### 3.3 File budget
| Asset                       | Budget                              |
|-----------------------------|-------------------------------------|
| Per-chapter ambience loop   | ≤ 200 KB (60s loop @ AAC 96 kbps)   |
| Transition resonance        | ≤ 30 KB (1.8s sub wash)             |
| Tactile micro-tone          | ≤ 20 KB (1.2s decay)                |
| Total audio per page (initial fetch) | ≤ 400 KB                   |

