## 4. Chapter Audio Behavior

Each chapter type has a default audio profile, declared in `audio.config.ts` alongside `atmosphere.config.ts`.

| Chapter type | Ambience              | Transition resonance | Tactile micro-tones |
|--------------|-----------------------|----------------------|---------------------|
| `hero`       | Distant urban edge / wind across glass | On entry (1.8s) | None                |
| `editorial`  | Room tone (interior, soft) | Subtle (1.2s)    | None                |
| `case`       | Project-specific recording (varies) | Mid (1.6s) | Allowed on slide advance (≤ -28 dB) |
| `human`      | Near-silence; subtle breath / wind | Almost imperceptible (0.8s wash) | Forbidden |
| `cultural`   | Place-specific field recording | Full (2.0s sub wash) | None         |
| `closing`    | Room tone fading to dead air | None — silence is the cut | None        |

### Chapter declaration
```ts
// components/chapters/CulturalChapter/audio.config.ts
import type { ChapterAudio } from "@/lib/sound/types";

export const audio: ChapterAudio = {
  ambience: {
    src: "/audio/cultural-monsoon-loop.m4a",
    peakLufs: -23,
    fadeInMs: 4000,
    fadeOutMs: 6000,
    duckOnTransition: 0.4,        // duck to 40% during cross-chapter
  },
  transitionResonance: {
    src: "/audio/transition-sub-warm.m4a",
    durationMs: 2000,
    triggerOn: "enter",
  },
  tactileMicroTones: {
    enabled: false,
  },
};
```

